26/03/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The State Electoral Commission decided Thursday (25 March) not to allow controversial former Defence Minister Ljube Boskovski to run in the 14 April presidential election. The commission said he has not lived in the country for the past ten years, as required. Boskovski, who has both Macedonian and Croatian citizenship, is a member of the main opposition VMRO-DPMNE, but decided to run as an independent.
In other news Thursday, the US Embassy in Skopje demonstrated its new system for collecting biometrical data from visa applicants. The fingerprint scanning system is being introduced in 75 US embassies and consulates worldwide, as a way to counter terrorism. (Dnevnik, Utrinski Vesnik - 26/03/04; Makfax - 25/03/04; Makfax, A1 TV - 24/03/04)
